<dl id="n40041b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40041b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40041b"> 41(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Hel / Loki / balder <font face="wake">D</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the German mythology the army of darkness is led by Hel, the personification of twilight, sunk to the goddess who enchains the dead and terrifies the living, and Loki, originally the god of fire, but afterwards &ldquo;looked upon as the father of the evil powers, who strips the goddess of earth of her adornments, who robs Thor of his fertilizing hammer, and causes the death of Balder the beneficent sun..cq <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 121</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
